In a continuing effort to show Americans the more literary and adult side of Osamu Tezuka's manga-graphic novels, Vertical proudly introduces Apollo's Song, the story of Shogo, a troubled young man who has no faith in love. When his misanthropy reaches its peak, he is met by the Goddess of Love, who condemns him to an eternity of heartbreak.

description: Danica travels where demons fear to tread - Heaven!

Neither wholly plant nor animal, neither entirely self-aware nor totally non-sentient, the creature called the Man-Thing is unique, unchanging and alone - but none who encounter him can ever be the same again. Empathic by nature and drawn to fight evil, his shambling visage inspires fear - and whatever knows fear burns at the Man-Thing's touch. Whether danger rises from the swamp or the city, the past or the future, outer space or the human soul, the Man-Thing awaits! Collecting ASTONISHING TALES (1970) #12-13; FEAR #11-18, and material from #10 and #19; MAN-THING (1974) #1-22, GIANT-SIZE MAN-THING #1-3 and material from #4-5, INCREDIBLE HULK (1968) #197-198; MARVEL TEAM-UP (1972) #68; MARVEL TWO-IN-ONE #43; MAN-THING (1979) #1-11; DR. STRANGE (1974) #41; and material from SAVAGE TALES (1971) #1, MONSTERS UNLEASHED #5 and #8-9, and RAMPAGING HULK (1977) #7.

description:
The summer may be hot, but Augusts YEN PLUS is here to cool you down!

Lord Maccon and Professor Lyall are taking a dip under the Thames in this months chapter of Soulless, and you wont believe what they find underwater! Meanwhile, Jacob and the Peculiars are in for a chilling surprise when they go searching for some answers about the mysterious death in town. Will and Tessa are in for their own frosty welcome from a certain warlock in the latest chapter of Infernal Devicesand who knows frosty better than Jack Frost, which continues in another TWO chapters this month!

Max and the flock join the girls of Soul Eater NOT! on vacation this month, but dont frettheres enough action packed in here to keep you chill all month long. So sit back, have some cake, and set sail with this months YEN PLUS!

Notice a new face? Or maybe you choose not to see anthing? This month YEN PLUS just got a little spookier with the first chapter preview of Another!

When Koichi Sakakibara transfers to Class 3-3 Yomiyama North Middle School, he finds himself hapless in the face of the unexplained weirdness of his classmates, a mysterious girl that no one else seems to recognize, and a strange curse that slowly begins to unravel

Max and the flock are still keeping coolmaybe too freakingly coolin the Antarctic, but when a spy is discovered amongst them, saving the world from global warming may have to take a back seat to the flock trying to save themselves! Finally coming face to face with the monster from Jacobs nightmares, Jacob and the peculiar children will have to fend for themselves in the next chapter of Miss Peregrines Home for Peculiar Children!

In the latest chapter of Infernal Devices, Gideon and Gabriel are given a proposition by Consul Wayland and Jem and Tessa have a new proposal of their own!

As Autumn creeps into the air, its time to cool down and fall into another jam-packed issue of YEN PLUS!
